{"cursor":"19469","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Popular culture' is the entirety of ideas, perspectives, attitudes,\nmemes, images, and other phenomena that are within the mainstream of\na given culture, especially Western culture of the early to mid 20th century and\nthe emerging global mainstream of the late 20th and early 21st century. Heavily\ninfluenced by mass media, this collection of ideas permeates the everyday lives\nof the society.\n\nPopular culture is often viewed as being trivial and dumbed-down in order to\nfind consensual acceptance throughout the mainstream. As a result, it comes\nunder heavy criticism from various non-mainstream sources (most notably\nreligious groups and countercultural groups) which deem it superficial,\nconsumerist, sensationalist, and corrupted.\n","linknr":381,"url":"Popular_culture","recorded":1362580426,"links":68,"instances":["cognitive","author","psychology","playwright"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Popular culture|","Media studies","Youth"],"headings":["History and definitions","Self-reference","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["perspective","cognitive"],["attitude","psychology"],["john_storey","author"],["john_storey","author"],["john_mcgrath","playwright"]],"members":["perspective","john_storey","attitude","john_mcgrath"],"related":["Idea","Perspective_(cognitive)","Attitude_(psychology)","Meme","Image","Phenomena","Mainstream","Cultural_anthropology","Western_culture","Globalization","Mass_media","Everyday_life","Society","Dumbing_down","Non-mainstream","Religious","Countercultural","Consumerist","Sensationalist","Johann_Heinrich_Pestaloz